channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Trump Team Just Levels Kamala With Perfect Reply to Their Anger Over Massive Musk Spaces Event
Anti-Israel protesters handed legal setback in effort to expand DNC rally
item.description: Pro-Palestinian demonstrators planning large protests in Chicago at next week's Democratic National Convention are facing a legal setback as they aim to march closer to the United Center.

item.title: House Dem Unveils Bill to Expand Secret Service Perimeter
item.description: Rep. Ritchie Torres, D-N.Y., introduced a bill Tuesday that would require the Secret Service to expand its security perimeter to 500 yards at public events, the latest in a series of bills he has authored to strengthen protection.

item.title: California Democrats Revive Legislation Allowing Murderers Sentenced to Life to Be Released Early
Close contest between Trump and Harris in this battleground state turned red: poll
item.description: A new poll suggests former President Trump holds a slim five-point advantage over Vice President Kamala Harris in the battle for Florida's 30 electoral votes.

item.title: NY Post: Dem Candidate John Avlon Got Manhattan Tax Abatements
item.description: Former CNN weekend anchor John Avlon's primary residency has come under further scrutiny amid reports that he missed tax payments while benefitting from almost $2,000 a year in abatements via a Manhattan residence.

item.title: NEW: Unearthed Video Shows Tim Walz Had Close Relationship With Hitler-Promoting Muslim Cleric
Musk boasts of 1B views for 'no limits' X interview with Trump
item.description: Tech billionaire Elon Musk said his "unscripted with no limits" interview with former President Trump on X garnered 1 billion views on Monday evening.

item.title: Abortion Measure on Ballot in Arizona
item.description: Voters in Arizona will decide on adding the right to an abortion to the state constitution in November.

item.title: Iran Says Only a Gaza Ceasefire Can Stop Their Attack on Israel
Minnesota grandma jailed for defying Walz COVID lockdown orders warns 'you do not want tyranny at this level'
item.description: A Minnesota grandmother and former small business owner jailed for defying Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz's COVID lockdown shares her story with America.

item.title: GOP Campaign Committee Scraps $700K in Ohio Senate Race Ads
item.description: The National Republican Senatorial Committee (NRSC) has scrapped more than $700,000 in cable ad reservations for the Ohio Senate race that were set to air this fall.

item.title: The Musk/Trump Conversation on X Shatters Records and Elon Posts Astounding Final Numbers
New Harris border security ads mark 180 from years of liberal immigration advocacy
item.description: The Harris campaign released an ad touting Vice President Kamala Harris' history of being "tougher" at the border as a prosecutor in California and as vice president.

item.title: Beto O'Rourke: 'Surprised' Harris Picked 'Good Guy' Walz
item.description: Former Rep. Beto O'Rourke said he's "really surprised" that Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz was picked as Democrat presidential nominee Kamala Harris' running mate because he's "so genuinely kind and nice."
